root.speaker: Square
root.message: Oh thank god.. that was just a dream! Now.. its time to teach my grandson his geometry lesson.

grandson one.speaker: Square's Grandson
grandson one.message: Hello grandpa! I have a quick question! You have been teaching me to raise numbers to the third power: I suppose 3 cubed must mean something in Geometry, what does it mean?

choices.text: Nothing at all... Not at least in Geometry; for Geometry has only Two Dimensions

grandson plea.speaker: Square's Grandson
grandson plea.message: But it must be that a Square of three inches every way, moving somehow parallel to itself (but I don't see how) must make something else (but I don't see what) of three inches every way...

choices.text: Go to bed! If you would talk less nonsense, you would remember more sense.

sphere's response.message: That boy is right! Three cubed does have an obvious meaning in Geometry!

choices.text: Where are you speaking from? Show yourself!

sphere2.message: {At first the being appears to be a line, and therefore a woman. However as the shape inexplicably grows, it becomes increasingly apparent that the shape is a circle that is growing through some unknown means.}

choices.text: Who are you? How and why did you enter my home?

sphere3.speaker: Circle?
sphere3.message: I am a sphere, and I come to teach you of the third dimension: height. The third dimension is how I entered your home.

choices.text: Proposterous! The only two dimensions are length and width!
A third dimension? Do you mean breadth or thickness?

length width.speaker: Sphere
length width.message: I came from the third dimension, that is how I just appeared before you. The third dimension is up above and down below...

choices.text: There is only two dimensions. What do you mean there is more?
Do you mean northward and southward?

breadth thickness.speaker: Sphere
breadth thickness.message: No, I do not mean breadth nor thickness. I mean up above and down below...

choices.text: I do not understand the nonsense you are spouting
Do you mean northward and southward?

north south.speaker: Sphere
north south.message: No, I do not mean northward and southward. I mean upward, in the direction perpendicular to the face of your square, or what you would call your inside. And no, I do not mean perpendicular to your eye...

analogy1.speaker: Sphere
analogy1.message: A Point is a creature having no dimensions; a Line is a creature of one dimension you are a Square, the same relation holds between you and me, for I am a Cube.

choices.text: How may I verify the existence of the third dimension?

analogy2.speaker: Sphere
analogy2.message: I shall touch your stomach, as to verify the existence of the third dimension.

choices.text: {Such an idea is intolerable. Scream for help, and attack with all of your might!}

disappear.speaker: Sphere
disappear.message: Listen: No stranger must witness what you have witnessed. If you refuse to listen to reason, then I suppose I must force reason upon you. Up you go...
